timeline
    title EU AI Act Enforcement Timeline (Regulation 2024/1689)
    section 2024
        10 Jun 2024 : Act enters into force
                    : 20 days after Official Journal publication
        1 Aug 2024  : Published in Official Journal of the EU
    section 2025
        2 Feb 2025  : Prohibited AI practices apply (Art. 5)
                   : Fines up to €35M or 7% global turnover
                   : AI literacy obligations (Art. 4)
        2 Aug 2025  : GPAI model obligations apply (Art. 53)
                   : Affects OpenAI, Anthropic, Google
                   : Governance & penalties chapters apply
    section 2026
        2 Feb 2026  : Commission guidelines on Art. 6 published
        2 Aug 2026  : MAJORITY of remaining rules apply
                   : High-risk system obligations for new deployments
                   : National AI regulatory sandboxes must be operational
                   : Digital Omnibus may delay some high-risk deadlines
    section 2027
        2 Aug 2027  : High-risk AI (Article 6.1) fully applies
                   : Legacy GPAI models must comply
    section 2030
        2 Aug 2030  : Public sector AI systems must comply
        31 Dec 2030 : Large-scale IT system AI components must comply
